  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "For the peri peri marinade, add all of the ingredients to a blender and season generously with salt and pepper – and I mean generously. Blitz until smooth. Marinate the chicken thighs in the sauce for a minimum of 1 hr (but ideally overnight) in a covered bowl."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "For the onion relish, peel and finely slice the red onions. Melt the butter and a splash of olive oil in a large pot and cook the onions with a big pinch of salt for 30-40 mins until sticky and soft. If they start to catch, just add in a splash of water and give it a good mix. Add the sugar and vinegar, then gently simmer for about 5 more mins until really sticky – give it a taste and adjust the vinegar and sugar to your liking. Set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "For the aioli, grate the garlic and zest and juice the lemon into the mayonnaise. Give it a good mix and season with salt and pepper. Done! Slice the halloumi and separate the romaine leaves."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat your grill to high. Remove the chicken from the fridge and bring it up to room temp for 20 mins, then transfer to a tray. Slide under the grill and cook for 20-25 mins until the chicken is cooked through and charred. In the meantime, heat 1 tbsp oil in a large pan over a medium heat and add the halloumi. Cook for 2 mins on each side until golden."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Time to assemble! Warm your pitta, then fill with aioli, chicken, halloumi, relish and lettuce. Voilà!"
    }
  ],
